<issue num="30" status="TC1">
<title>Wrong header for LC_*</title>
<section><sref ref="[locale.category]"/></section>
<submitter>Nathan Myers</submitter>
<date>6 Aug 1998</date>

<discussion>
<p>Paragraph 2 implies that the C macros LC_CTYPE etc. are defined in &lt;cctype&gt;,
where they are in fact defined elsewhere to appear in &lt;clocale&gt;. </p>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<p>In <sref ref="[locale.category]"/>, paragraph 2, change
&quot;&lt;cctype&gt;&quot; to read &quot;&lt;clocale&gt;&quot;. </p>
</resolution>

</issue>
